353 static int32_t MmwDemo_RFParser_setAoAParams
354 (
355  MmwDemo_RFParserOutParams *outParams,
356  bool *pFoundValidProfile,
357  int16_t frameTotalChirps,
358  uint16_t *validChirpTxEnBits,
359  bool bpmEnabled
360 )
361 {
362  uint32_t chirpLoopIdx;
363  bool validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp = false;
364  uint16_t validProfileTxEn = 0;
365  int32_t retVal = 0;
366  int32_t i;
367 
368 
369  /* for this antenna pattern we require that all Rx's are enabled */
370  if (outParams->numRxAntennas != SYS_COMMON_NUM_RX_CHANNEL)
371  {
372  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_EINVAL__NUM_RX_ANTENNAS;
373  goto exit;
374  }
375 
376  /* now loop through unique chirps and check if we found all of the ones
377  needed for the frame and then determine the azimuth/elevation antenna
378  configuration
379  */
380  if (*pFoundValidProfile==true) {
381  for (chirpLoopIdx = 0; chirpLoopIdx < frameTotalChirps; chirpLoopIdx++)
382  {
383  bool validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp = false;
384  uint8_t log2TxEn;
385  uint16_t chirpTxEn = validChirpTxEnBits[chirpLoopIdx];
386  if (chirpTxEn == 0) {
387  /* this profile doesn't have all the needed chirps */
388  *pFoundValidProfile = false;
389  break;
390  }
391 
392  /* If only TX antenna is enabled, then its 0x1<< log2TxEn should equal chirpTxEn */
393  log2TxEn = mathUtils_floorLog2(chirpTxEn);
394  validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp = (chirpTxEn == (1 << log2TxEn));
395 
396  /* for this antenna pattern we require that only one Tx per chirp is enabled*/
397  if (validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp != true)
398  {
399  /* this profile doesn't have chirps with one TxAnt enabled per Chirp */
400  *pFoundValidProfile = false;
401  break;
402  }
403 
404  /* if this is the first chirp, record the chirp's
405  MIMO config as profile's MIMO config. We dont handle intermix
406  at this point */
407  if (chirpLoopIdx == 0)
408  {
409  validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp = validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp;
410  }
411  /* check the chirp's MIMO config against Profile's MIMO config */
412  if (validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp != validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp)
413  {
414  /* this profile doesnt have all chirps with same MIMO config */
415  *pFoundValidProfile = false;
416  break;
417  }
418 
419  /* save the antennas actually enabled in this profile */
420  validProfileTxEn |= chirpTxEn;
421  }
422  }
423 
424  /* found valid chirps for the frame; mark this profile valid */
425  if (*pFoundValidProfile == true) {
426  uint16_t tempValidProfileTxEn=0;
427 
428  /* set Tx Antenna and Virtual antenna related config */
429  outParams->numTxAntennas = 0;
430  tempValidProfileTxEn = validProfileTxEn;
431  while (tempValidProfileTxEn!=0) {
432  if ((tempValidProfileTxEn&0x1)==0x1)
433  {
434  outParams->numTxAntennas++;
435  }
436  tempValidProfileTxEn=tempValidProfileTxEn>>1;
437  }
438  if (outParams->numTxAntennas > SYS_COMMON_NUM_TX_ANTENNAS)
439  {
440  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_EINVAL_NUM_TX_ANTENNAS;
441  goto exit;
442  }
443  outParams->numVirtualAntAzim = 0; // unused
444  outParams->numVirtualAntElev = 0; // unused
445  outParams->numVirtualAntennas = outParams->numTxAntennas * outParams->numRxAntennas;
446  /* Sanity Check: Ensure that the number of antennas is within system limits */
447  if ((outParams->numVirtualAntennas <= 0) ||
448  (outParams->numVirtualAntennas > (SYS_COMMON_NUM_TX_ANTENNAS * SYS_COMMON_NUM_RX_CHANNEL)))
449  {
450  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_EINVAL__NUM_VIRTUAL_ANTENNAS;
451  }
452 
453  /* txAntOrder[] will be needed for Rx Channel Phase Measurement/Compensation routines */
454  for (i = 0; i < outParams->numTxAntennas; i++)
455  {
456  outParams->txAntOrder[i] = mathUtils_floorLog2(validChirpTxEnBits[i]);
457  }
458 
459  outParams->validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp = validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp;
460  }
461 
462 exit:
463  return (retVal);
464 }
465 
466 
467 #else

486 static int32_t MmwDemo_RFParser_setAoAParams
487 (
488  MmwDemo_RFParserOutParams *outParams,
489  bool *pFoundValidProfile,
490  int16_t frameTotalChirps,
491  uint16_t *validChirpTxEnBits,
492  bool bpmEnabled
493 )
494 {
495 
496  uint32_t chirpLoopIdx;
497  bool validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp = false;
498  uint16_t validProfileTxEn = 0;
499  int32_t retVal = 0;
500  bool validProfileHasElevation = false;
501  int32_t i;
502 
503 
504  /* now loop through unique chirps and check if we found all of the ones
505  needed for the frame and then determine the azimuth/elevation antenna
506  configuration
507  */
508  if (*pFoundValidProfile==true) {
509  int16_t nonElevFirstChirpIdx = -1;
510  for (chirpLoopIdx = 0; chirpLoopIdx < frameTotalChirps; chirpLoopIdx++)
511  {
512  bool validChirpHasElevation = false;
513  bool validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp = false;
514  uint16_t chirpTxEn = validChirpTxEnBits[chirpLoopIdx];
515  if (chirpTxEn == 0) {
516  /* this profile doesn't have all the needed chirps */
517  *pFoundValidProfile = false;
518  break;
519  }
520 
521  /* check if this is an elevation TX chirp - if yes, it is assumed to be 4Rx, 3Tx case */
522  validChirpHasElevation = (chirpTxEn == MmwDemo_RFParserHwCfg.elevTxAntMask);
523  validProfileHasElevation |= validChirpHasElevation;
524 
525  /* if not, then check the MIMO config */
526  if (!validChirpHasElevation)
527  {
528  uint8_t log2TxEn;
529 
530  if(bpmEnabled)
531  { /* In case of BPM, check if both TX antennas are enabled*/
532  if(chirpTxEn != MmwDemo_RFParserHwCfg.azimTxAntMask)
533  {
534  /* The frame is configured as BPM but this chirp does not enable both TX antennas*/
535  *pFoundValidProfile = false;
536 #ifdef MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_DBG
537  System_printf("Bad BPM configuration. chirpTxEn=%d for chirp %d \n",chirpTxEn,chirpLoopIdx);
538 #endif
539  break;
540  }
541  }
542  else
543  {
544  /* If only TX antenna is enabled, then its 0x1<< log2TxEn should equal chirpTxEn */
545  log2TxEn = mathUtils_floorLog2(chirpTxEn);
546  validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp = (chirpTxEn == (1 << log2TxEn));
547  }
548 
549  /* if this is the first chirp without elevation, record the chirp's
550  MIMO config as profile's MIMO config. We dont handle intermix
551  at this point */
552  if (nonElevFirstChirpIdx == -1) {
553  validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp = validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp;
554  nonElevFirstChirpIdx = chirpLoopIdx;
555  }
556 
557  /* if this is the first chirp, record the chirp's
558  MIMO config as profile's MIMO config. We dont handle intermix
559  at this point */
560  if (chirpLoopIdx == 0)
561  {
562  validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp = validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp;
563  }
564  /* check the chirp's MIMO config against Profile's MIMO config */
565  if (validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp != validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp)
566  {
567  /* this profile doesnt have all chirps with same MIMO config */
568  *pFoundValidProfile = false;
569  break;
570  }
571  }
572 
573  /* save the antennas actually enabled in this profile */
574  validProfileTxEn |= chirpTxEn;
575  }
576  }
577 
578  /* found valid chirps for the frame; mark this profile valid */
579  if (*pFoundValidProfile == true) {
580  uint32_t numTxAntAzim = 0;
581  uint32_t numTxAntElev = 0;
582 
583  outParams->numTxAntennas = 0;
584  if (validProfileHasElevation)
585  {
586  numTxAntElev = 1;
587  }
588 
589  if (bpmEnabled == true)
590  {
591  /* BPM eanbled */
592  numTxAntAzim = 2;
593  }
594  else if (validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp == true)
595  {
596  uint8_t log2TxEn;
597 
598  while(validProfileTxEn)
599  {
600  log2TxEn = mathUtils_floorLog2(validProfileTxEn);
601  if ((0x1 << log2TxEn) & MmwDemo_RFParserHwCfg.azimTxAntMask)
602  {
603  numTxAntAzim++;
604  }
605  validProfileTxEn &= ~(0x1<< log2TxEn);
606  }
607  }
608  else /* i.e. SIMO case, all chirps have same one Tx antenna. */
609  {
610  /* in this case, for AOA, Tx Azimuth antenna is only 1. */
611  if ((validProfileTxEn & MmwDemo_RFParserHwCfg.azimTxAntMask) != 0)
612  {
613  numTxAntAzim = 1;
614  }
615  else
616  {
617  numTxAntAzim = 0;
618  }
619  }
620 
621 #ifdef MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_DBG
622  System_printf("Azimuth Tx: %d (MIMO:%d), Elev Tx:%d\n",
623  numTxAntAzim,validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp,numTxAntElev);
624 #endif
625 
626  outParams->numTxAntennas = numTxAntAzim + numTxAntElev;
627  if (outParams->numTxAntennas > SYS_COMMON_NUM_TX_ANTENNAS)
628  {
629  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_EINVAL_NUM_TX_ANTENNAS;
630  goto exit;
631  }
632 
633  outParams->numVirtualAntAzim = numTxAntAzim * outParams->numRxAntennas;
634  outParams->numVirtualAntElev = numTxAntElev * outParams->numRxAntennas;
635  outParams->numVirtualAntennas = outParams->numVirtualAntAzim +
636  outParams->numVirtualAntElev;
637 
638  /* Sanity Check: Ensure that the number of antennas is within system limits */
639  if ((outParams->numVirtualAntennas <= 0) ||
640  (outParams->numVirtualAntennas > (SYS_COMMON_NUM_TX_ANTENNAS * SYS_COMMON_NUM_RX_CHANNEL)))
641  {
642  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_EINVAL__NUM_VIRTUAL_ANTENNAS;
643  }
644 
645  /* txAntOrder[] will be needed for Rx Channel Phase Measurement/Compensation routines */
646  if (validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp)
647  {
648  for (i = 0; i < outParams->numTxAntennas; i++)
649  {
650  outParams->txAntOrder[i] = mathUtils_floorLog2(validChirpTxEnBits[i]);
651  }
652  }
653  else
654  {
655  for (i = 0; i < outParams->numTxAntennas; i++)
656  {
657  outParams->txAntOrder[i] = i;
658  }
659  }
660 
661  outParams->validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp = validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp;
662 
663 #ifdef MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_DBG
664  System_printf("Ant setting virtualAzim: %d , virtual Elev :%d\n",
665  outParams->numVirtualAntAzim, outParams->numVirtualAntElev);
666 #endif
667  }
668 
669 exit:
670  return (retVal);
671 }
672 
673 #endif

695 static int32_t MmwDemo_RFParser_parseCtrlConfig
696 (
697  MmwDemo_RFParserOutParams *outParams,
698  uint8_t subFrameIdx,
699  MMWave_OpenCfg *openCfg,
700  MMWave_CtrlCfg *ctrlCfg,
701  float rfFreqScaleFactor,
702  bool bpmEnabled
703 )
704 {
705  uint16_t frameChirpStartIdx;
706  uint16_t frameChirpEndIdx;
707  int16_t frameTotalChirps;
708  uint32_t profileLoopIdx, chirpLoopIdx;
709  bool foundValidProfile = false;
710  uint16_t channelTxEn = openCfg->chCfg.txChannelEn;
711  uint8_t channel;
712  uint8_t numRxAntennas;
713  uint16_t numLoops;
714  int32_t retVal = 0;
715  int32_t errCode;
716  float bandwidth, centerFreq, adcStart, slope, startFreq;
717 
718  /***********************************************
719  * Sanity Check on ADC configuration
720  ***********************************************/
721  /* Only support 16 Bits ADC out bits */
722  if(openCfg->adcOutCfg.fmt.b2AdcBits != 2U)
723  {
724  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_ENOTSUPPORT__NON_16BITS_ADC;
725  goto exit;
726  }
727 
728  /* Only support complex ADC data format */
729  if((openCfg->adcOutCfg.fmt.b2AdcOutFmt != 1U) &&
730  (openCfg->adcOutCfg.fmt.b2AdcOutFmt != 2U))
731  {
732  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_ENOTSUPPORT__NON_COMPLEX_ADC_FORMAT;
733  goto exit;
734  }
735 
736  /***********************************************
737  * Parse openCfg
738  ***********************************************/
739  /* Find number of enabled channels */
740  numRxAntennas = 0U;
741  for (channel = 0U; channel < SYS_COMMON_NUM_RX_CHANNEL; channel++)
742  {
743  if(openCfg->chCfg.rxChannelEn & (0x1U << channel))
744  {
745  outParams->rxAntOrder[numRxAntennas] = channel;
746  /* Track the number of receive channels: */
747  numRxAntennas++;
748  }
749  else
750  {
751  outParams->rxAntOrder[channel] = 0U;
752  }
753 
754  //add check to make sure lambda/2
755  //check for rxAnt -= 1, 2, 4 and their limitations
756  }
757  outParams->numRxAntennas = numRxAntennas;
758 
759 
760 
761  /***********************************************
762  * Parse frameCfg
763  ***********************************************/
764  /* Read frameCfg chirp start/stop index */
765  frameChirpStartIdx = MmwDemo_RFParser_getChirpStartIdx(ctrlCfg, subFrameIdx);
766  frameChirpEndIdx = MmwDemo_RFParser_getChirpEndIdx(ctrlCfg, subFrameIdx);
767  numLoops = MmwDemo_RFParser_getNumLoops(ctrlCfg, subFrameIdx);
768  outParams->framePeriod = MmwDemo_RFParser_getFramePeriod_ms(ctrlCfg, subFrameIdx);
769  frameTotalChirps = frameChirpEndIdx - frameChirpStartIdx + 1;
770 
771  /* TODO::Advance Frame only support one burst - chain limitation, */
772  if (ctrlCfg->dfeDataOutputMode == MMWave_DFEDataOutputMode_ADVANCED_FRAME)
773  {
774  if(ctrlCfg->u.advancedFrameCfg.frameCfg.frameSeq.subFrameCfg[subFrameIdx].numOfBurst != 1)
775  {
776  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_ENOTSUPPORT__NON_ONE_NUMOFBURST_FOR_ADVANCED_FRAME;
777  goto exit;
778  }
779  }
780 
781  /* since validChirpTxEnBits is static array of 32 */
782  if(frameTotalChirps > 32U)
783  {
784  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_ENOIMPL__NUM_UNIQUE_CHIRPS_MORE_THAN_32;
785  }
786 
787  /* loop for profiles and find if it has valid chirps */
788  /* we support only one profile in this processing chain */
789  for (profileLoopIdx = 0;
790  ((profileLoopIdx < MMWAVE_MAX_PROFILE) && (foundValidProfile == false));
791  profileLoopIdx++)
792  {
793  uint32_t mmWaveNumChirps = 0;
794  uint16_t validChirpTxEnBits[32]={0};
795  MMWave_ProfileHandle profileHandle;
796 
797  profileHandle = MmwDemo_RFParser_getProfileHandle(ctrlCfg, profileLoopIdx);
798  if (profileHandle == NULL)
799  continue; /* skip this profile */
800 
801  /* get numChirps for this profile; skip error checking */
802  retVal = MMWave_getNumChirps(profileHandle, &mmWaveNumChirps, &errCode);
803  if (retVal != 0)
804  {
805  retVal = errCode;
806  goto exit;
807  }
808 
809  /* loop for chirps and find if it has valid chirps for the frame
810  looping around for all chirps in a profile, in case
811  there are duplicate chirps
812  */
813  for (chirpLoopIdx = 1; chirpLoopIdx <= mmWaveNumChirps; chirpLoopIdx++)
814  {
815  MMWave_ChirpHandle chirpHandle;
816  retVal = MMWave_getChirpHandle(profileHandle, chirpLoopIdx, &chirpHandle, &errCode);
817  if (retVal != 0)
818  {
819  retVal = errCode;
820  goto exit;
821  }
822  /* get handle and read ChirpCfg */
823  {
824  rlChirpCfg_t chirpCfg;
825  retVal = MMWave_getChirpCfg(chirpHandle, &chirpCfg, &errCode);
826  if (retVal != 0)
827  {
828  retVal = errCode;
829  goto exit;
830  }
831  {
832  uint16_t chirpTxEn = chirpCfg.txEnable;
833  /* do chirps fall in range and has valid antenna enabled */
834  if ((chirpCfg.chirpStartIdx >= frameChirpStartIdx) &&
835  (chirpCfg.chirpEndIdx <= frameChirpEndIdx) &&
836  ((chirpTxEn & channelTxEn) > 0))
837  {
838  uint16_t idx = 0;
839  for (idx = (chirpCfg.chirpStartIdx - frameChirpStartIdx);
840  idx <= (chirpCfg.chirpEndIdx - frameChirpStartIdx); idx++)
841  {
842  validChirpTxEnBits[idx] = chirpTxEn;
843  foundValidProfile = true;
844  }
845  }
846  }
847  }
848  }
849 
850  /* now parse through all valid chirps, check if the profile is valid and then set the AoA related parameters */
851  retVal = MmwDemo_RFParser_setAoAParams(outParams,
852  &foundValidProfile,
853  frameTotalChirps,
854  validChirpTxEnBits,
855  bpmEnabled);
856  if (retVal != 0)
857  {
858  goto exit;
859  }
860 
861  /* found valid chirps for the frame; set remaining parameters */
862  if (foundValidProfile == true) {
863  rlProfileCfg_t profileCfg;
864 
865  outParams->validProfileIdx = profileLoopIdx;
866  /* Get the profile configuration: */
867  retVal = MMWave_getProfileCfg(profileHandle,&profileCfg, &errCode);
868  if (retVal != 0)
869  {
870  retVal = errCode;
871  goto exit;
872  }
873 
874 #ifndef MMW_ENABLE_NEGATIVE_FREQ_SLOPE
875  /* Check frequency slope */
876  if (profileCfg.freqSlopeConst < 0)
877  {
878  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_ENOTSUPPORT__NEGATIVE_FREQ_SLOPE;
879  goto exit;
880  }
881 #endif
882  /* set other parameters */
883  outParams->numAdcSamples = profileCfg.numAdcSamples;
884  outParams->numRangeBins = mathUtils_pow2roundup(outParams->numAdcSamples);
885  outParams->numChirpsPerFrame = frameTotalChirps * numLoops;
886 
887  outParams->numDopplerChirps = outParams->numChirpsPerFrame/outParams->numTxAntennas;
888  outParams->numDopplerBins = mathUtils_pow2roundup(outParams->numDopplerChirps);
889 
890  adcStart = ((float)profileCfg.adcStartTimeConst * 10.f * 1.e-9);
891  startFreq = (float)profileCfg.startFreqConst/(float)(1U << 26)*rfFreqScaleFactor*(float)1e9;
892  slope = (float)profileCfg.freqSlopeConst * ((rfFreqScaleFactor*1e3*900.f)/(float)(1U << 26)) * 1e12;
893  bandwidth = (slope * outParams->numAdcSamples)/(profileCfg.digOutSampleRate * 1e3);
894  centerFreq = startFreq + bandwidth * 0.5f + adcStart * slope;
895  outParams->chirpInterval = (float)(profileCfg.idleTimeConst + profileCfg.rampEndTime)/1000.*10*1.e-6;
896 
897  outParams->rangeStep = (MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_SPEED_OF_LIGHT_IN_METERS_PER_SEC * profileCfg.digOutSampleRate * 1e3) /
898  (2.f * slope * outParams->numRangeBins);
899  outParams->rangeResolution = (MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_SPEED_OF_LIGHT_IN_METERS_PER_SEC * profileCfg.digOutSampleRate * 1e3) /
900  (2.f * slope * outParams->numAdcSamples);
901 
902  outParams->dopplerStep = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_SPEED_OF_LIGHT_IN_METERS_PER_SEC /
903  (2.f * outParams->numDopplerBins * outParams->numTxAntennas *
904  centerFreq * outParams->chirpInterval);
905  outParams->dopplerResolution = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_SPEED_OF_LIGHT_IN_METERS_PER_SEC /
906  (2.f * outParams->numChirpsPerFrame * centerFreq * outParams->chirpInterval);
907 
908 #ifdef MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_DBG
909  System_printf("Ant setting virtualAzim: %d , virtual Elev :%d\n",
910  outParams->numVirtualAntAzim, outParams->numVirtualAntElev);
911  System_printf("startFreqConst: %d\n", profileCfg.startFreqConst);
912  System_printf("rfFreqScaleFactor: %f\n", rfFreqScaleFactor);
913  System_printf("bandwidth : %f GHz\n", bandwidth*1.e-9);
914  System_printf("adcStartTimeConst: %d\n", profileCfg.adcStartTimeConst);
915  System_printf("freqSlopeConst: %d\n", profileCfg.freqSlopeConst);
916  System_printf("centerFreq: %f GHz\n", centerFreq*1.e-9);
917  System_printf("dopplerStep: %f\n", outParams->dopplerStep);
918  System_printf("adcStart: %f us\n", adcStart * 1e6);
919  System_printf("slope: %f GHz\n", slope*1.e-9);
920  System_printf("startFreq: %f GHz\n", startFreq*1.e-9);
921 #endif
922 
923  }
924  }
925 
926  if (foundValidProfile == false)
927  {
928  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_EINVAL__VALID_PROFILECFG_NOT_FOUND;
929  goto exit;
930  }
931 
932 exit:
933  return (retVal);
934 }
935 
950 static int32_t MmwDemo_RFParser_parseADCBufCfg
951 (
952  MmwDemo_RFParserOutParams *outParams,
953  MmwDemo_ADCBufCfg *adcBufCfg
954 )
955 {
956  uint16_t numBytePerSample = 0;
957  uint32_t chirpThreshold;
958  uint32_t maxChirpThreshold;
959  uint32_t bytesPerChirp;
960  int32_t retVal = 0;
961 
962  /* Only support Complex */
963  if (adcBufCfg->adcFmt != 0)
964  {
965  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_ENOTSUPPORT__NONCOMPLEX_ADC_FORMAT;
966  goto exit;
967  }
968 
969  /* Complex dataFormat has 4 bytes */
970  numBytePerSample = 4U;
971 
972  /* Calculate RX channel data size and make it align to 16 bytes */
973  outParams->adcBufChanDataSize = outParams->numAdcSamples * numBytePerSample;
974  outParams->adcBufChanDataSize = (outParams->adcBufChanDataSize + 15U) / 16U * 16U;
975 
976  /* Calculate max possible chirp threshold */
977  bytesPerChirp = outParams->adcBufChanDataSize * outParams->numRxAntennas;
978 
979  /* find maximum number of full chirps that can fit in the ADCBUF memory, while
980  also being able to divide numChirpsPerFrame, we do not want remainder processing */
981  maxChirpThreshold = MmwDemo_RFParserHwCfg.adcBufSize/ bytesPerChirp;
982  if (maxChirpThreshold >= outParams->numChirpsPerFrame)
983  {
984  maxChirpThreshold = outParams->numChirpsPerFrame;
985  if (maxChirpThreshold > SYS_COMMON_CQ_MAX_CHIRP_THRESHOLD)
986  {
987  /* If CQ monitor is enabled, then check max chirpthreshold */
988  maxChirpThreshold = SYS_COMMON_CQ_MAX_CHIRP_THRESHOLD;
989  }
990  }
991  else
992  {
993  /* Find largest divisor of numChirpsPerFrame no bigger than maxChirpThreshold */
994  while (outParams->numChirpsPerFrame % maxChirpThreshold)
995  {
996  maxChirpThreshold--;
997  }
998  }
999 
1000  /* ADCBuf control function requires argument alignment at 4 bytes boundary */
1001  chirpThreshold = adcBufCfg->chirpThreshold;
1002 
1003  /* if automatic, set to the calculated max */
1004  if (chirpThreshold == 0)
1005  {
1006  chirpThreshold = maxChirpThreshold;
1007  }
1008  else
1009  {
1010  if (chirpThreshold > maxChirpThreshold)
1011  {
1012 #ifdef MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_DBG
1013  System_printf("Desired chirpThreshold %d higher than max possible of %d, setting to max\n",
1014  chirpThreshold, maxChirpThreshold);
1015 #endif
1016  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_EINVAL__CHIRP_THRESH_GREATER_THAN_MAX_ALLOWED;
1017  goto exit;
1018  }
1019  else
1020  {
1021  /* check for divisibility of the user provided threshold */
1022  if((outParams->numChirpsPerFrame % chirpThreshold) != 0)
1023  {
1024  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_ENOTSUPPORT__NON_DIVISIBILITY_OF_CHIRP_THRESH;
1025  goto exit;
1026  }
1027  else
1028  {
1029  /* Chirp threshold has a valid configuration */
1030  }
1031  }
1032  }
1033 
1034 #ifdef MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_DBG
1035  System_printf(" chirpThreshold %d max = %d, \n",
1036  chirpThreshold, maxChirpThreshold);
1037 #endif
1038 
1039  /* Save chirpThreshold */
1040  outParams->numChirpsPerChirpEvent = chirpThreshold;
1041 
1042 exit:
1043  return (retVal);
1044 }

1071 int32_t MmwDemo_RFParser_parseConfig
1072 (
1073  MmwDemo_RFParserOutParams *outParams,
1074  uint8_t subFrameIdx,
1075  MMWave_OpenCfg *openCfg,
1076  MMWave_CtrlCfg *ctrlCfg,
1077  MmwDemo_ADCBufCfg *adcBufCfg,
1078  float rfFreqScaleFactor,
1079  bool bpmEnable
1080 )

1083

1085  {
1086  /* Parse the profile and chirp configs and get the valid number of TX Antennas */
1087  retVal = MmwDemo_RFParser_parseCtrlConfig(outParams, subFrameIdx,
1088  openCfg, ctrlCfg, rfFreqScaleFactor, bpmEnable);
1089 
1090  if (retVal != 0)
1091  {
1092  goto exit;
1093  }
1094  retVal = MmwDemo_RFParser_parseADCBufCfg(outParams, adcBufCfg);
1095  if (retVal != 0)
1096  {
1097  goto exit;
1098  }
1099  }
1100  else
1101  {
1102  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_EINVAL__NUM_SUBFRAMES;
1103  }
1104 
1105 exit:
1106  return retVal;
1107 }
